race.comment: Very even contest. IT'S A WONDER (7) was beaten less than three lengths in the Group 3 Belle Of The Turf two runs back over the mile at Gosford. Struggled last start when stretched out to 1800m. Can bounce back in this far more suitable contest. BAT OUT OF HELL (1) is as honest as they come but hasn't won in ages. Backs up seven days after racing on the speed and being swamped late to finish a close fifth over this course and distance. In the money at six of seven previous efforts over 1550m here. Can bounce back. HOUSE OF CARDS (9) was a little one-paced over 1400m at Warwick Farm last start. Fitter for three runs back from a spell and is looking for this sort of trip now. CLYDE (3) has been a bit flat so far this prep but can improve third-up with the winkers going on. IVAN'S HERO (10) was beaten by a smart one last time. Looks very well in after Grima's claim so he must come under notice.
